                        supply chain value. In two decades of close watch, we have observed the industry appreciating
                        out of mediocrity to a structured profitable service business, and a performing corporate
                        business unit. Hence, adding value to the overall organisational growth and the national
                        economy.
                        The drivers of change include the rising global and regional insecurity and the awareness of
                        potential risk by the public, the increasing demand for highly skilled risk management
                        professionals with the relevant education and training, and intense competition by the growing
                        number of service providers. In addition, technology advancement and process improvement from
                        the old traditional security methods which relied on isolation (security-by-obscurity) as the
                        preferred risk mitigation strategy, to a well-defined, well-designed, and well-implemented
                        integrated physical protection security system. Thus, enabling the value of the Internet of
                        Things (IoT). Not only is this convergence in security helping information technology and
                        operational technology managers to improve productivity, but also, increasing operating
